The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 18, 2004 				 TMB upbeat on growth 
																								Chennai, Feb. 17 (PTI): With Sterling group chief C. Sivasankaran deciding to exit Tamilnad Mercantile Bank (TMB) by selling his 33 per cent stake, the bank is identifying individuals from within the Nadar community who could buy the shares in bulk by December.																								A bright future awaits the bank. It is all set to scale new heights in the most professional manner and achieve a 100 per cent growth by next fiscal, said Ramachandra Adityan of the Nadar Forum. The forum represents the community that originally promoted the bank.																								Adityan signed a crucial share-transfer agreement on Monday with A. Subramanian of the Sterling group. 
